        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Q: What is fear kiting and the other ways we kill?

A1: Fear kiting is when you darkness (snare) a mob, then cast fear on it.  The mob walks away slowly while you put DoTs on it, and your pet beats it to death.  This is the most common way for a necro to kill things.

If quarters are too tight to fear kite use one of these:
A2: Root Rott, is when you darkness a mob, then root it (or a veriant of root).  You then cast non-DD DoTs on the mob and wait for it to die.  Use this method if you can't use the next one.

A3: Pet Tank, is when you pull a mob and have your pet tank it while you cast DoTs on it and heal your pet.  Use a HP Drain DoT on the mob, and then use a pact spell on you pet to keep him alive.  Careful of aggro.  You may need to FD after you get your DoTs on the mob so he doesn't come after you.  Make sure you Drain spell lands and is workign before you cast your pact spell (most embarasing way to die).

A4: Rott then Pet Tank.  Simple, if the mob will totally trash your pet, but you want the extra damage Root Rott the mob for a while, then send in your pet at 50% or whatever is safe for him to live through.  If you time it right, you won't have to heal him or 1 heal will be suficiant.

-DV

<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137300 "> <font size=-1 color=red>Darkvane</a></font> * 55 Dark Elf <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com">Defiler</a>
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
      </tr>

