        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Question: Does Iksar Regen make for a better class of Necromancer?</P><P>Answer: No. In my oppinion, DE is still the best. Why?</P><P>1: Ultravision > Infravision. Nothing is better than being able to see all the time.<BR>2: Although it is easy enough to get INT gear, it saves money by having a higher starting INT.<BR>3: It is a cake walk to get to 51 now since there are no more hell levels pre-52. So putting 3 AAs into Regen will up your regen anyway. I know because I just went from 1 to 51 in about 3 weeks of moderate playing.<BR>4: Yes an Iksar Regen will be even greater with AAs, however, as a DE you will up your regen, and you won't have the XP penalty of an Iksar. 52-60 is a bear as it is, why make it worse?</P><P>Question: Is Iksar a bad Race?</P><P>Answer: No. Iksars have many advantages. However, with XP penalties they are a lot more work. I have grouped with Iksar before with my DE and gotten up to 2 levels to 1. Generally it's somewhere about 1 1/2 to 1. You may not notice that much of a difference to start with, but over the course of a few levels you will notice that the DE gains a huge lead on the Iksar.</P><P>Once again it's a choice that only you can make, and I am the type of person that would make a Gnome ShadowKnight just to be different.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - megadeth22 on 09/29/2002  13:43:27</P><P>Edited by - megadeth22 on 09/29/2002  13:44:55</font></td>
